How to Install OsourCL
1. Preparation — Install Dependencies
bashpip install cryptography aiohttp

2. Create a Folder & Place the File
C_OsourCL/
└── OsourCL.py ← place the file here
Or you can place it in any folder, for example, D:\OsourCL\ on Windows or ~/OsourCL/ on Linux/Mac.

3. Run for the First Time
bashcd C_OsourCL
python OsourCL.py
The terminal will display:
╔═ ... 
║ OsourCL - Cloud Component Motherboard ║
╚═════════════════════ ═════════════════════╝

  ✅ New API Key Generated:

  osourcl_Ex1WmHPsl3KTuMq5Zk5TRO...

  ⚠️ Save this key!
The C_OsourCL/ folder is automatically created and contains:
C_OsourCL/
├── cloud_storage/ ← where files are stored
├── data/
│ ├── api_keys.json ← API keys are stored here
│ ├── config.json
│ └── metrics.json
├── logs/
│ ├── osourcl.log
│ ├── security.log
│ └── audit.log
└── backups/

4. Use in Other Python Scripts
pythonfrom OsourCL import OsourCL

ocl = OsourCL()
ocl.start()

# Upload file
meta = ocl.upload("file.bin")
print(meta["id"]) # Use this ID for download

# Download
ocl.download(meta["id"], "output.bin")

# Translate binary
result = ocl.translate("program.exe", mode="both")

# Connect EXE to cloud
key = ocl.generate_api_key("app_name")
ocl.connect_exe("program.exe", key)

# Connect APK to cloud
ocl.connect_apk("app.apk", key)
Make sure OsourCL.py is in the same folder or add its path:
pythonimport sys
sys.path.insert(0, "C:/path/to/C_OsourCL")
from OsourCL import OsourCL

5. Check Status & Quota
pythonocl = OsourCL()
ocl.start()
print(ocl.status()) # all system info
print(ocl.get_quota()) # storage usage
print(ocl.list_api_keys()) # list API keys

System Requirements
Item Minimum: Python 3.8+ RAM: 512 MB (for 10GB files using streaming), Disk space according to the file being stored (max 10GB), OS: Windows / Linux / macOS, Package cryptography, aio/http, Sonnet 4.6 Low, 10GB or higher
